  "text": "NCAT2 [CITATION_1] , a rat mAb against ctN-catenin, was used for production of other mAbs to this protein. Immunoprecipitates with NCAT2 were obtained from chick brain lysates as described below. Rats were immunized with these materials (20 brain samples per rat), and their splenocytes were used for production of hybridomas. From the hybridomas thus obtained, three mAbs, NCAT3, 4, and 5, were isolated. All of them reacted with chick, mouse, and rat ctN-catenin and recognized two isoforms of this molecule (Uchida et al., 1995) . NCAT4 and 5 reacted specifically with aN-catenin but not with ctE-catenin, but NCAT3 crossreacted with aE-catenin. We mainly used NCAT5 for immunohistochemistry, and NCAT2 for immunoblotting and immunoprecipitation.",
